Figure 1(a) depicts the crystal structure of Sr4(Ru1−xMnx)3O10 for x = 0.23 and 0.41, with the indication of two Ru/Mn ((Ru/Mn)1 and (Ru/Mn)2) sites and four O (O1, O2, O3, O4) sites. Compared to the undoped case (x = 0) as shown in the right of Fig. 1(a), both the number of Ru/Mn and O sites are reduced. The change from orthorhombic for x = 0 to tetragonal for x = 0.23, and 0.41 indicates the removal of octahedral rotation upon Mn doping. While a (b) (the values for parent compound are divided by \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
