The above electrical and magnetic properties indicate that the Mn-doped Sr4(Ru1−xMnx)3O4 (x = 0.34 and 0.41) is a ferromagnetic semiconductor with a narrow energy gap. This sets it apart from other sister compounds with Mn doping and adds a new member in a small magnetic semiconductor family. Further evidence for ferromagnetic semiconducting properties of Sr4(Ru1−xMnx)3O4 (x = 0.34 and 0.41) is reflected in magnetoresistance (MR). Figure 4(a–d) show, for x = 0.34, the field dependence of the MR for I//ab and H//I (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
